{"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"A wrapper that you use to integrate an AppKit view controller into your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"OpenSwiftUI interface.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"attribute","text":"@preconcurrency"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NSViewControllerRepresentable"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/Body-swift.associatedtype","text":"Body","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP4BodyQa"},{"kind":"text","text":" == "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Never","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5NeverO"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/NSViewControllerRepresentable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance to create and manage an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/appkit\/nsviewcontroller","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object in your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI interface. Adopt this protocol in one of your app’s custom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instances, and use its methods to create, update, and tear down your view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"controller. The creation and update processes parallel the behavior of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI views, and you use them to configure your view controller with your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"app’s current state information. Use the teardown process to remove your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view controller cleanly from your OpenSwiftUI. For example, you might use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"teardown process to notify other objects that the view controller is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disappearing."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add your view controller into your OpenSwiftUI interface, create your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSViewControllerRepresentable"},{"type":"text","text":" instance and add it to your OpenSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interface. The system calls the methods of your custom instance at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appropriate times."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system doesn’t automatically communicate changes occurring within your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view controller to other parts of your OpenSwiftUI interface. When you want your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view controller to coordinate with other OpenSwiftUI views, you must provide a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/NSViewControllerRepresentable\/Coordinator","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance to facilitate those"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interactions. For example, you use a coordinator to forward target-action"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and delegate messages from your view controller to any OpenSwiftUI views."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"warning","name":"Warning","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI fully controls the layout of the AppKit view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"controller’s view using the view’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/appkit\/nsview\/1483713-frame"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/appkit\/nsview\/1483817-bounds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"properties. Don’t directly set these layout-related properties on the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"managed by an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSViewControllerRepresentable"},{"type":"text","text":" instance from your own"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"code because that conflicts with OpenSwiftUI and results in undefined behavior."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"protocol","platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15"}],"remoteSource":{"fileName":"NSViewControllerRepresentable.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUI\/Integration\/Representable\/AppKit\/NSViewControllerRepresentable.swift#L57"},"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSViewControllerRepresentable","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:11OpenSwiftUI29NSViewCont